	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=204418"><span id=" ">mfbrownbear</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">23 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I just bought one of these in bazaar for 5pp yesterday! I would never have bought or camped one otherwise. It seems to be mainly a necro weapon, but for the price I paid it makes a great skull-topped whoop-a$$ stick.<br/>I know, for an enchanter the -CHA is terrible, but with a +25 CHA Opal Encrusted Stein in the secondary slot it doesn't hurt. Now that I have it, and am of a level for the proc to trigger, I love it! I will use it whenever I need to raise 1H Blunt.<br/>And for my 2cp on caster melees: One technique for enchanters in melee after level 20 is to chain-stun using our Color series of spells. They are AE stuns centered on the caster, and the range is short so you have to be within melee range. Since you are in melee range anyway and there's really no time to med between casting stuns, you may as well have auto-attack on and get a few whacks in and hopefully a proc or two. Chain-stunning saves a LOT of health by keeping the mob stunned almost every second. Due to the mana drain from chain-casting I don't recommend this unless you have KEI, or if your healer is OOM and you want to give your tank a breather.<br/>I should say, I will only equip this when I'm raising 1H Blunt or using the above technique, or kiting. I usually have my Stein of Moggok and either my Opal Encrusted Stein or a +INT weapon in hand.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Abigaille Lafey - Enchantress on Tholuxe Paells</td></tr>
